From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: ack EDMA misc IRQ status (W1C)

The EDMA misc interrupt handler only counts errors and never acks the
MISC_INT_STAT register, and edma_enable_misc_interrupt() unmasks without
clearing any pending status. On IPQ5332 a latched misc condition (observed
when the WAN/eth1 RTL8221B PHY is linked at boot) then fires the instant the
misc IRQ is unmasked and re-fires forever -> IRQ storm -> RCU stall, which
manifests as a hang inside the final regmap_write of edma_setup().

Clear (W1C) any pending status before unmasking, and ack the handled status
in the handler so a latched condition cannot storm the CPU.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/edma.c
@@ -314,7 +314,16 @@ static void edma_enable_misc_interrupt(v
 {
 	struct ppe_device *ppe_dev = edma_ctx->ppe_dev;
 	struct regmap *regmap = ppe_dev->regmap;
-	u32 reg;
+	u32 reg, stat;
+
+	/* clear any latched misc status (W1C) before unmasking.
+	 * The handler doesn't ack the status, so a pending condition (correlates
+	 * with the WAN PHY connected at boot) would fire on unmask and re-fire
+	 * forever -> IRQ storm -> RCU stall in this very write. */
+	reg = EDMA_BASE_OFFSET + EDMA_REG_MISC_INT_STAT_ADDR;
+	regmap_read(regmap, reg, &stat);
+	if (stat)
+		regmap_write(regmap, reg, stat);
 
 	reg = EDMA_BASE_OFFSET + EDMA_REG_MISC_INT_MASK_ADDR;
 	regmap_write(regmap, reg, edma_ctx->intr_info.intr_mask_misc);
@@ -397,6 +406,11 @@ static irqreturn_t edma_misc_handle_irq(
 		u64_stats_update_end(&stats->syncp);
 	}
 
+	/* ack the handled misc status (W1C) so a latched
+	 * condition does not re-fire immediately and storm the CPU. */
+	reg = EDMA_BASE_OFFSET + EDMA_REG_MISC_INT_STAT_ADDR;
+	regmap_write(regmap, reg, misc_intr_status);
+
 	return IRQ_HANDLED;
 }
 
